SQL injection:
    1. Code injection technique which might destroy the database
    2. One of the most common web hacking techniques
    3. is the placement of malicious code in SQL statements
       using web page input

    It can be used to retrieve hidden data, where we can modify an
    SQL query to return additional results.
    Subverting application logic, where you can change a query to
    interfere with the application's logic.

    UNION attacks, where you can retrieve data from different
    database tables.